  "text": "Our main variable of interest is intelligence as measured by national IQs. The data come from [CITATION_1] . In their first study, Lynn and Vanhanen (2002) Table 1 , we cluster countries the countries by their average index of cognitive abilities and find that life satisfaction is increasing with nation's IQ. Sources: The data on IQ come from [CITATION_2] ; The data on life satisfaction come from Helliwell et al. (2015) We also control for GDP per capita, as economic development is positively correlated with intelligence [CITATION_3] and life satisfaction [CITATION_4] . Moreover, GDP per capita is also associated with improved living standards, higher wages and technological improvements;",
